olive oil
2 potato
1 cucumber
2 bunch spring onion
½ bunch baby broccoli
3 clove garlic
1 packet pork loin steaks
1 sachet Sweet Soy Seasoning
1 packet oyster sauce
1 packet Plum Sauce
6 bao buns
1 packet mayonnaise
1 bunch Asian Greens

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
Cut potato into fries.
• Place on a lined oven tray. Season with salt,
drizzle with olive oil and toss to coat.
• Spread out evenly, then bake until tender,
20-25 minutes.

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
Cut potato into fries.
• Place on a lined oven tray. Season with salt,
drizzle with olive oil and toss to coat.
• Spread out evenly, then bake until tender,
20-25 minutes.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil
over medium-high heat. Cook baby broccoli
until tender, 5-6 minutes.
• Add Asian greens and remaining garlic, and
cook until fragrant, 1-2 minutes.
• Remove pan from heat, add oyster sauce and
toss to combine. Transfer to a serving plate and
cover to keep warm.

• Wipe out the frying pan and return to
medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
When oil is hot, cook pork in batches, tossing,
until golden, 2-3 minutes.
• Remove pan from heat, return all pork to the
pan and add plum sauce, tossing to coat

• Place bao buns on a plate with a small splash of
water (just a small splash so they stay fluffy!).
• Cover with cling wrap or a microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave on high, 1 minute. Set aside to cool
slightly, 1 minute.

• Gently halve bao buns and spread with
mayonnaise. Fill with sticky plum pork,
cucumber and spring onion.
• Serve with potato fries and oyster sauce greens.
Enjoy!